statement:
\emph{Sketch a single function satisfying all of the listed criteria.}

\begin{enumerate}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item
  $\displaystyle f(3) = 0$
\item
  $\displaystyle f'(3) < 0$
\item
  $\displaystyle f''(3) > 0$
\end{enumerate}

sols:
A simple-like parabola with a zero at three will work. The other zero
one can be anywhere, for no particular reason lets make it at 5. So the
function

\[\displaystyle f(x) = (x-3)(x-5) = x^{2} -8x + 15\] satisfies all three
conditions.

To double check,

\begin{align*}
f(3) &= (3-3)(3-5) = 0 \\
f'(3) &= 2(3)-8 = -2 <0  \\
f''(3) &= 2 > 0 \\
\end{align*}

Let's see the picture

